namedLocations.description: A ZIP Code is a postal code used by the United States Postal Service (USPS) in a system it introduced in 1963. The term ZIP is an acronym for Zone Improvement Plan; it was chosen to suggest that the mail travels more efficiently and quickly (zipping along) when senders use the code in the postal address. The basic format consists of five digits. An extended ZIP+4 code was introduced in 1983 which includes the five digits of the ZIP Code, followed by a hyphen and four additional digits that reference a more specific location.

transcript.text: Welcome to on Print Shop in Orders we will see how to add a new order or a offline order.
To add a new order or a offline order, you will need to select a customer.
It can be a existing customer or you can add a new customer.
Then choose a product add payment and shipping method and confirm the order.
To add a new order, you will need to go to admin panel Orders Add new order.
Before proceeding further, let's understand the utility of this feature.
So suppose you have a customer who is a walk in customer and for that customer you need to add a order.
Or if a customer sends an e-mail to add a order on his behalf or he calls you and says that please add a order on my behalf.
So in that case you can add a new order from here.
You can add a offline order from here that can be your existing customer or a new customer.
So in that case, you can select the customer from select customer over here.
You can either search the existing customer by name or e-mail from here or you can add a new customer by clicking on this add customer button in the right hand side.
Here you can add the customer details for the new customer and click on 7 continue and add a new order or a offline order.
Or you can just type a name or e-mail address of the customer and select a customer if it is a existing customer.
So here I have selected the customer Richard Henry.
Now you can select the shipping address from here or click on Manage addresses to manage the shipping address.
In the same way you can select the billing address from here.
Or you can click on Manage addresses to manage the billing addresses.
After this just click on Next button.
Here you will need to choose the product.
So you can choose a product that can be existing product or a custom product.
If you select existing product then you can select the product from a drop down.
Let's select this product.
After selecting the product from here, you can change the artwork name.
Then you will need to add the details like say quantity, product weight, production days, additional information or additional options.
And you can upload artwork from upload file button over here.
And you need to add the product price.

Now either you can add this detail manually or you can just click on online price calculator, select the product size, quantity and other additional options, whichever you want to select or you need to select and after selecting all the details you have over here the option apply only options.
So in that case it will apply only additional options or you can click on apply all and it will apply every details including the price.
So I will click on apply all.
So you can see all the details are added like say quantity, size, then production days, additional options.
It has been added over here and the product price is added over here.
So after adding the product, you can either click on save and add another product if you need to add another product to this order or just simply click on save and continue.
So let us see how you can add another product.
So I click on save and add another product.
Here I select another product.
Say for example I select mouse pad again I will select the online price calculator, select the details over here and apply all and now the second product is selected by me.
You can see already the one product is existing I am selecting the another product.
Now I will click on save and continue.
So now 2 product is added to the single order.
After that you need to add the shipping method and the payment method.
So you can select shipping method from here like say UPS Ground.
Then you can select the payment method from here.
If you need, you can add the additional comments over here.
Then order amount.
You can see the order amount details over here.
If you want to change, you can change it manually from here.
If you need to raise a payment request, you can activate this payment request button.
Otherwise keep it inactive.
Here you can see the card product details.
Here you have the product details.
You can edit the product details from this edit button if required.
Shipping address you can manage from here by Manage Addresses.
Billing address you can manage from here by clicking on Manage addresses and after selecting and adding all the details you will need to click on confirm order to place the order.
So once I have clicked on confirm order you can see the order is placed.

Order number is 1056 and the customer will receive a thank you e-mail of placing the order and when customer logs in to the storefront under my account, he will be able to see the order details like say here is the order number 1056.
When I click on view button you'll be able to see all the order details.
So this is how you can add a new order or a offline order.
Thank you for watching this video.
